    <h2>U.S. Supreme Court</h2>
    <h1>McIver v. Wattles, 22 U.S. 650 (1824)</h1>
    <h2>McIver v. Wattles</h2>
    <h2>22 U.S. (9 Wheat.) 650</h2>
    <h2>ERROR TO THE CIRCUIT COURT</h2>
    <h2>FOR THE DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA</h2>
    <h2>Syllabus</h2>
    <p>Where the writ of error is dismissed for want of jurisdiction, no costs are allowed.</p>
    <p>MR. CHIEF JUSTICE MARSHALL said that in all cases where the cause is dismissed for want of jurisdiction, no costs are allowed.</p>
    <p>Motion denied.</p>
  </opinion>
